# Canonical: # Source: Curated from Microsoft Excel (es-ES) error literal spellings.
# Note: Spanish Excel error literals can use leading inverted punctuation (e.g. `#¡VALOR!`,
# `#¿NOMBRE?`). The formula engine does not currently accept these spellings when parsing localized
# formulas, so `src/locale/registry.rs` intentionally does not translate them yet; we still record
# the real Excel spellings here as upstream truth.
